title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 19, ch. XXX - Repealed
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 19, ch. XXX - Repealed

State Regulations

Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 19, ch. XXX
Chapter XXX of Title 19 NYCRR was promulgated pursuant to

Executive Order No. 10 entitled "Directing filing of financial statements by
certain officers and employees within the Executive Department," dated May 22, 1975. Executive Order No. 10 was revoked and superseded by Executive Order No. 3, entitled "Establishing A Board of Public Disclosure," dated January 28, 1983. Executive Order No. 117, entitled "Abolishing the Board of Public

Disclosure," dated December 28, 1988, abolished the Board of Public Disclosure
as of January 1, 1989. The regulations found in Chapter XXX of Title 19 NYCRR
are therefore without force and effect and were deleted on January 15, 1998, effective immediately. State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
